## New to GitHub?

Start here:

- **Start here (Markdown):**  
  https://github.com/PeterHIggins19/huf_core_github_v1.1.8_no_inputs/blob/main/docs/start_here.md

- **Start here (DOCX record copy):**  
  https://github.com/PeterHIggins19/huf_core_github_v1.1.8_no_inputs/raw/main/docs/start_here.docx

One-click setup scripts (in repo root):

- **Windows:**  
  https://github.com/PeterHIggins19/huf_core_github_v1.1.8_no_inputs/blob/main/START_HERE_WINDOWS.bat

- **macOS:**  
  https://github.com/PeterHIggins19/huf_core_github_v1.1.8_no_inputs/blob/main/START_HERE_MAC.command

- **Linux:**  
  https://github.com/PeterHIggins19/huf_core_github_v1.1.8_no_inputs/blob/main/start_here_linux.sh

These create a local Python environment, install dependencies, and fetch **Markham + Toronto** inputs.
Planck is guided/manual because the FITS files are very large.

---

## The HUF system (three parts)

1) **Handbook:**  
   https://github.com/PeterHIggins19/huf_core_github_v1.1.8_no_inputs/blob/main/docs/handbook.md

2) **Reference Manual:**  
   https://github.com/PeterHIggins19/huf_core_github_v1.1.8_no_inputs/blob/main/docs/reference_manual.md

3) **GitHub package:** this repo (library + CLI + tests + cases + artifacts)

**Data statement:** all Markham data is real, all Planck data is real, and all Toronto traffic data is real.
